        <h2 class="title"><a href="/node/291">Theology Rocks Show 066 - &quot;What&#039;s in Your Bible?&quot;</a> <span id="nodetoggle-291" style="cursor: pointer; " title="show details for Theology Rocks Show 066 - &quot;What&#039;s in Your Bible?&quot;"></span></h2>        <div id="collapsinode-291">
        <div class="content"><p>Sometimes we get confused between <b>our Bible</b> (KJV, NIV, NASB, NLT, NET, ASV, <i>ad infinitum</i>). Our point is that none of those are <b>The Bible</b>. Throw in <i>The Message</i>, the <i>Living Bible</i> and company, and you're compounding translation problems with paraphrase. Toss in some presuppositions, some flawed teaching and a pinch (or more) of pride, and you get problems aplenty.</p>
<p>Our point is, "there's more to the Bible than your translation."</p>
<p>There are a whole mess of great tools online that we didn't even mention in the podcast:</p>
</div>
    <span class="submitted"></span>
