  <div class="node">
        <h2 class="title"><a href="/node/252">Theology Rocks Show  #61 - &quot;False Teachings, the Damage They Do to the Church and Dealing With Them&quot;</a> <span id="nodetoggle-252" style="cursor: pointer; " title="show details for Theology Rocks Show  #61 - &quot;False Teachings, the Damage They Do to the Church and Dealing With Them&quot;"></span></h2>        <div id="collapsinode-252">
        <div class="content"><p>In 1 Timothy chapter 4, Paul talks to the young pastor about teachings that erode the joy of the gospel, steal from the Church and make the truth that the Church teaches look needlessly foolish. &quot;Godless myths and old wives&#39; tales&quot; that are to be avoided. We should instead train ourselves to be godly. How many times has the Church been dragged into debates about good things that should be outlawed, when everything God has made is good?</p>
<p> Somebody has to stop the nonsense, and in doing so, we can save both ourselves and our hearers. </p>
</div>
    <span class="submitted"></span>
    <span class="taxonomy"><ul class="links inline"><li class="first taxonomy_term_239"><a href="/taxonomy/term/239" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_239">false teachings</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_237"><a href="/taxonomy/term/237" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_237">pastors</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_9"><a href="/taxonomy/term/9" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_9">Show</a></li>
<li class="last taxonomy_term_6"><a href="/taxonomy/term/6" rel="tag" title="The Theology Rocks podcast -- Truths to Stand On" class="taxonomy_term_6">Theology Rocks</a></li>
</ul></span>
