  <div class="node">
        <h2 class="title"><a href="/node/247">Theology Rocks Show #58 - &quot;The Danger of Keeping Your Past in Front of You&quot;</a> <span id="nodetoggle-247" style="cursor: pointer; " title="show details for Theology Rocks Show #58 - &quot;The Danger of Keeping Your Past in Front of You&quot;"></span></h2>        <div id="collapsinode-247">
        <div class="content"><p>Words of wisdom from Pumba: &quot;Put your behind in the past!&quot; </p>
<p>For many Christians, our testimony is the list of terrible things in our past that God saved us from.There&#39;s a danger in keeping those memories in front of us (prominent in our minds). There comes a time in our lives that we just have to &quot;put our past behind us,&quot; and move on. It doesn&#39;t mean those things aren&#39;t real, that we should deny them, or that God doesn&#39;t intend to use those things to minister to others.</p>
</div>
    <span class="submitted"></span>
    <span class="taxonomy"><ul class="links inline"><li class="first taxonomy_term_230"><a href="/taxonomy/term/230" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_230">past</a></li>
